{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"InputDeviceInfo","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/InputDeviceInfo","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Media_Capture_and_Streams_API\">Media Capture and Streams API</a></strong></li><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/InputDeviceInfo\"><code>InputDeviceInfo</code></a></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Methods</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/InputDeviceInfo/getCapabilities\"><code>getCapabilities()</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Inheritance:</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MediaDeviceInfo\"><code>MediaDeviceInfo</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Related pages for Media Capture and Streams</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/CanvasCaptureMediaStreamTrack\"><code>CanvasCaptureMediaStreamTrack</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLCanvasElement/captureStream\"><code>HTMLCanvasElement.captureStream()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MediaDevices\"><code>MediaDevices</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MediaDevices/getUserMedia\"><code>MediaDevices.getUserMedia()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MediaStream\"><code>MediaStream</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MediaStreamTrack\"><code>MediaStreamTrack</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MediaStreamTrackEvent\"><code>MediaStreamTrackEvent</code></a></li><li><a class=\"page-not-created\" title=\"The documentation about this has not yet been written; please consider contributing!\"><code>MediaTrackCapabilities</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MediaTrackConstraints\"><code>MediaTrackConstraints</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MediaTrackSettings\"><code>MediaTrackSettings</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MediaTrackSupportedConstraints\"><code>MediaTrackSupportedConstraints</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/mediaDevices\"><code>Navigator.mediaDevices</code></a></li><li><a class=\"page-not-created\" title=\"The documentation about this has not yet been written; please consider contributing!\"><code>VideoStreamTrack</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>The <strong><code>InputDeviceInfo</code></strong> interface of the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Media_Capture_and_Streams_API\">Media Streams API</a> gives access to the capabilities of the input device that it represents.</p>\n<p><code>InputDeviceInfo</code> objects are returned by <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MediaDevices/enumerateDevices\"><code>MediaDevices.enumerateDevices()</code></a> if the returned device is an audio or video input device.</p><svg viewBox=\"-1 -1 650 42\" preserveAspectRatio=\"xMinYMin meet\">\n  <a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" xlink:href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MediaDeviceInfo\">\n    <rect x=\"0\" y=\"0\" width=\"120\" height=\"25\" fill=\"#fff\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" stroke-width=\"2px\"></rect>\n    <text x=\"60\" y=\"16\" font-size=\"10px\" fill=\"#4D4E53\" text-anchor=\"middle\">\n      MediaDeviceInfo\n    </text>\n  </a>\n  <line x1=\"120\" y1=\"14\" x2=\"150\" y2=\"14\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" \"=\"\"></line>\n  <polyline points=\"120,14 130,9 130,19 120,14\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" fill=\"#fff\"></polyline>\n  <a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" xlink:href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/InputDeviceInfo\" aria-current=\"page\">\n    <rect x=\"150\" y=\"0\" width=\"120\" height=\"25\" fill=\"#F4F7F8\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" stroke-width=\"2px\"></rect>\n    <text x=\"210\" y=\"16\" font-size=\"10px\" fill=\"#4D4E53\" text-anchor=\"middle\">\n      InputDeviceInfo\n    </text>\n  </a></svg>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"methods","title":"Methods","isH3":false,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"inputdeviceinfo.getcapabilities\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/InputDeviceInfo/getCapabilities\"><code>InputDeviceInfo.getCapabilities()</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Returns a <code>MediaTrackCapabilities</code> object describing the primary audio or video track of a device's <code>MediaStream</code>.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":"<p>The following example gets all media devices with <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MediaDevices/enumerateDevices\"><code>MediaDevices.enumerateDevices()</code></a>. If any of the devices are input devices then <code>console.log(device)</code> will print an <code>InputDeviceInfo</code> object to the console.</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code>navigator<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>mediaDevices<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">enumerateDevices</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">then</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">devices</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    devices<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">forEach</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">device</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>device<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// an InputDeviceInfo object if the device is an input device, otherwise a MediaDeviceInfo object.</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-main/#dom-inputdeviceinfo","title":"Media Capture and Streams"}],"query":"api.InputDeviceInfo"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.InputDeviceInfo","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/InputDeviceInfo/bcd.json"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Methods","id":"methods"},{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"}],"summary":"The InputDeviceInfo interface of the Media Streams API gives access to the capabilities of the input device that it represents.","popularity":0.0003,"modified":"2022-09-09T05:14:42.000Z","source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/inputdeviceinfo","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/api/inputdeviceinfo/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/277e5969c63b97cfb55ab4a0e612e8040810f49b","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/InputDeviceInfo","title":"InputDeviceInfo"}],"pageTitle":"InputDeviceInfo - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false}}